reviewText:
Oh, I'm sneeeaky..!

It's about:stealth, ambush and dirty tricks;
turn-based combat or/and real-time attacks from behind.
Why you should play this:game offers light RPG-elements (levelling up your skills and buying special equipment in store);
regardless its non-complex nature gameplay is exciting - there's an option:
to have a direct fight;
wait in an ambush;
quietly pass through the whole level without having a single combat;
use special equipment or level's enviroment to distract an enemy or lead it into a trapon some levels there're simple puzzles (where to go or how to get in particular zone) - unfortunately, such levels are scarce.
Why you may not like it:it's short - 15 levels will pass faster than you think;
most of the levels (not all) are linear: you simply go from one room" to another.
Being sneaky...
Being sticky...
Who will care
Rubies picking ?"
